turn.6: The Nevill Baronetcy, of Holt in the County of Leicester, was created in the Baronetage of England on 25 May 1661 for Thomas Nevill.
turn.8: The title became extinct on his death in 1712.
turn.10: The Nevill Baronetcy, of Grove in the County of Nottingham, was created in the Baronetage of England on 24 February 1675 for Edward Nevill, subsequently Member of Parliament for East Retford.
turn.11: Who was the Member of Parliament?
turn.12: He was a descendant of Sir Robert Nevill, of Eldon, fourth son of Ralph Neville, 2nd Baron Neville de Raby (great-uncle of Ralph de Neville, 1st Earl of Westmorland).
